        public boolean has(@CheckForNull

      • get

        public T get(@CheckForNull
    Object key)
        Find and return the reference object for given key, or return a default value when the object is not found.

        The default value is implementation dependent and must not be null.

        This implementation calls find(key, defaultValue), where the defaultValue is the parameter passed to the constructor. If the result is not null, return the result. Otherwise throws LookupException.

        Specified by:
        get in interface Lookup<T>
        Parameters:
        key - the key to lookup the object
        Returns:
        the reference object found or the defaultValue passed to the constructor if not found

      • hunt

        public T hunt(Object key)
        Find and return the reference object for given key, or fail if one doesn't exist.

        hunt distinguish itself from get and find methods by throwing exception when the reference object cannot be found.

        This implementation triggers exception when key is null or lookup(Object) returns null. Otherwise, delegates to lookup and return the value.

        Specified by:
        hunt in interface Lookup<T>
        Parameters:
        key - the key to lookup the object
        Returns:
        the reference object found
